The article provides a transcript of a press conference held by Department of Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg and FAA Administrator Mike Whitaker regarding holiday travel and the threats posed by the Houthis in the Red Sea. Secretary Buttigieg discusses the record travel demand during Thanksgiving, low cancellation rates, and the Department of Transportation's efforts to ensure airlines are prepared for significant travel demand during the holidays. He also mentions the Department of Transportation's recent announcement that Southwest Airlines will pay penalties and provide passenger relief for last year's holiday travel meltdown. Administrator Whitaker discusses Operation Prosperity Guardian, a multinational security initiative to counter Houthi attacks on shipping in the Red Sea. He mentions the formation of an international coalition and the condemnation of Houthi threats by multiple countries. The transcript also includes questions from reporters on various topics such as the designation of the Houthis as a terrorist organization, the involvement of Saudi Arabia and the UAE in the Red Sea initiative, and the release of American hostages in Venezuela.